                            <comment id="12951325" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 17 Mar 2009 09:29:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have committed a unit test showing the bug&lt;br/&gt;
Committed revision 755163.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.apache.camel.processor.ChoiceNoErrorHandlerTest&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug is not fixed yet, only a test to show the bug&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951323" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 17 Mar 2009 12:41:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lowering priority to major.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug is only manifested when&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;disabled error handler = noErrorHandler (not default)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;disabled JMX (not default)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12951334" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 17 Mar 2009 16:24:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Its the &lt;tt&gt;InstrumentationErrorHandlerWrappingStrategy&lt;/tt&gt; that is the culprint.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With JMX enable camel context gets this strategy added that skips interceptors.&lt;br/&gt;
But with no JMX we do not have a such a strategy and thus a default error handler is added&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12951285" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 18 Mar 2009 07:05:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes got it now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Trunk: Committed revision 755487.&lt;br/&gt;
1.x: Committed revision 755493.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
